Anadolu to Shut Basketball Team if Names Rejected, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-04T06:04:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/anadolu-to-shut-basketball-team-if-names-rejected-hurriyet-says.html
Anadolu Holding, owner of the Middle
East’s biggest brewer, will close its Efes Pilsen basketball
team in  Turkey  if proposed new names are rejected, Hurriyet
newspaper reported, citing Chief Executive Tuncay Ozilhan.   The company is proposing either "Efes" or "Anadolu Efes"
and won’t accept any other options, Ozilhan said, according to
the Istanbul-based newspaper. New legislation has barred alcohol
advertising in sports.  Anadolu Holding has $800 million to invest this year and
plans to increase capacity in its operations outside Turkey as
well as energy investyments in Georgia and Turkey, the newspaper
said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
